# {{botany}} A weed, ''[[Capsella]] bursa-pastoris'', family ''[[Brassicaceae]]'', native to Europe but now found world-wide. The seeds, leaves and roots are edible, and it is said to have medicinal properties. Its seed pod, when moistened, exudes a sticky substance to which insects can become stuck, and thus, the plant has been used as a natural means of [[pest]] control.